[thinking] **Evaluating class loading in native runtime**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how ClassLoader resources work in a native runtime environment. So, if classes aren't on the file system, can native image tests still run executable files with compiled classpath resources? It makes me wonder if dynamic tests could be executed. I think there might be test classes available on the classpath, but a native executable typically doesn’t include class files as resources unless specifically configured. I guess the native-image test runner could possibly include test classes.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Evaluating test discovery**
[thinking] 
