 require classes to be public. I'll also have to consider any Checkstyle implications.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting classpath in reports**\\n\\nI think I should take a closer look at the classpath in the previous test reports. It’s essential to ensure everything is set correctly, and I might find some discrepancies or insights that could be useful. Checking the classpath might help me understand any issues better or lead me to improve my approach in the future. Let's see what I can find in those reports and how they relate to current tests!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_F5Afo1xIlHNjigDSYcRUvbP6|fc_05a031c3e22e6398016a284bc660dc8197bc3e6f23adeb5ffd", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build/reports/tests/test/classes -type f -maxdepth 1 -print | head -20 && rg \"junit-jupiter\" -n tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build/reports tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build/tmp 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2100, "output": 1910, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41386, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781025672897, "responseId": "resp_05a031c3e22e6398016a284b8962388197acad9b523ce2aa9b"}}
