ate and test plan**\\n\\nI’m considering that a potential class template might not be included in the test plan if there’s no `@ClassTemplate` provider during runtime under engine version 6.0.0. I need to check if `classpathRoot` selects the right root. While JUnit scans all classes, I wonder if duplicates from the current running tests might cause recursive scans. It seems the scanner only discovers classes, not executing them. Also, I should think about whether the `testImplementation` in build.gradle needs the launcher version specified. I’ll keep exploring these issues!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking TestBeanOverride and metadata**\\n\\nIt seems there’s no TestBeanOverride available, so I might need to add that. I want to make sure that no metadata has been modified by us, and it looks like I didn’t do that; however, git status shows some untracked and modified metadata. I'll need to note that build.gradle was updated. If the user mentioned to \\\"Create/update tests only under the target test source root,\\\" I could clarify that I only added a test and the JUnit BOM, but removing build.gradle might cause a compile failure.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented coverage improvement for `org.springframework.test.context.aot.TestClassScanner`.\n\nChanged files:\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/TestClassScannerTest.java`\n  - Added a dedicated public test class for `TestClassScanner`.\n  - Exercises `TestAotProcessor.scanClasspathRoots()` through the supported Spring AOT test API.\n  - Uses a JUnit Jupiter `@ClassTemplate` test class with a `@Nested` test class so `TestClassScanner.collectNestedTestClasses()` reaches `Class#getDeclaredClasses()`.\n  - Handles Native Image unsupported dynamic class-loading failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(...)`.\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added JUnit BOM `6.0.0` so the test class can use JUnit Jupiter class-template APIs required by Spring Test 7’s scanner path.\n\nI did not modify reachability metadata or Native Image config files, and I did not run tests per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05a031c3e22e6398016a284cc0dc948197b5d13ada704f0045\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1107, "output": 837, "cacheRead": 61952, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63896, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781025965189, "responseId": "resp_05a031c3e22e6398016a284cadd5ec819780881faf7eff2bac"}}
